        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1241",
        "content": "Let no trace of emotion be visible on your countenance, bear your grief as the cloud bears within it ruin and death-a fatal secret, known only when the storm bursts. Go, my friend, reserve your strength for the moment when the crash shall come.\"",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
